summary: Sometimes you can have science fiction where you create a whole other world, like Star Wars. The genesis was Apocalypse Now. It...
body:
Sometimes you can have science fiction where you create a whole other world, like Star Wars. The genesis was Apocalypse Now. It was supposed to be George Lucas’s movie at first. George Lucas and Francis Ford Coppola, they came up from LA to the Bay Area because it was the hotbed of radicalism. They wanted to make a radical film collective. And they didn’t. But after Lucas did American Graffiti, he was like, “Cool, I have a hit. Now I’m doing my Apocalypse Now,” which was his movie based on Heart of Darkness.

The protagonists were [supposed to be] the Vietcong — we were following them, going into enemy territory, into the US’s conquered territory, and finding their Kurtz, which was someone who had come from the Vietcong, joined up with the US, risen in the ranks because of everything he knew and how murderous he was against his own people, and they were going to go get him.

He couldn’t get it funded. He was like, “What? I just made all this money? What’s going on?” They were like, “It’s too radical. You’re not going to get this funded. Leave it alone.” He was like, “Okay, I’ll take the same story and I’ll put it in space.” The Rebels were the Vietcong, the Empire was the US, and Darth Vader was their Kurtz.

Boots Riley

by MidnightMew

The four of them are an extremely rag tag group of people with nothing in common but circumstance and an immense hatred of the first order. Yet somehow it works. Somehow, they haven’t managed to blow up the ship just yet, though there had been a rather close call that one time. They’ve come to an unspoken agreement that they don’t talk about that.

summary: Mace Windu survived, and is hunting Vader
body:
Mace Windu survived, and is hunting Vader

I mean, if Maul could survive what Obi Wan did to him.

Alas, Mace was pretty badly messed up by things, so he’s barely hanging on, but he is. And he’s constantly 2 steps behind Vader.

“My Lord Vader, we have finished subduing Calrissian’s loyalists from Cloud City, and it’s fully under our control, but…”

“But what, commander?”

“An unknown ship just landed, the only identifying marking being “BFM” painted on the side.”

“Ummm… Yep, Cloud City is under control, not need here anymore, gotta go! Force things and such, you wouldn’t understand!”

blog.title: Foammander X
blog.description: Aspiring Serviceman. Fighter. Artist. Writer. Reader. Props-maker. Cosplayer. “Viam Inviniemus”

body:
Clone Wars Appreciation Post

Star Wars: The Clone Wars is my favorite animated series because it wasn’t just an epic struggle, but captured every aspect of warfare, politics and the military.

It had:

-Diplomatic Tensions, with non-aligned soldiers paying the price (The Tulz vs Pantora)

-Humanitarian Aid (The Wolfpack with R2 and Threepio)

-Failed Ceasefires (Heroes on Both Sides)

-Training Indigenous natives to fight proxy wars (Onderon)

-asking reinforcements from allied systems (the Gungan reinforcements on Mon Cala)

-Military spending and the Military Industrial Complex (creation of 5M new troopers)

-Pacifism (Maridun)

-Installation of an unstable democracy (R2 and C3PO)

-defending the homeland (Kamino)

-surviving the cut (Domino Squad)

-Free will and the ethics of using a slave army (The Deserter)

-use of WMDs (Zillo Beast)

-Piracy and Bounty-Hunting (Hondo and Boba Fett)

-Use of child soldiers (Ahsoka)

-conflict between following orders and saving lives (Umbara)

-working with organized crime for the War Effort (rescuing Jabba’s son)

-PTSD (Rex’s flashbacks in Rebels)

-conspicuous gallantry above and beyond the call of duty (Commander Thorn)

-soldiers being men (79’s bar/“Bill it to the Republic”)

-soldiers being family men (Cut Lawquane/The Deserter)

-love vs duty (Obi-Wan and Satine)

-Manipulation of the tide of War (Palpatine’s plan)

-Treatment of POWs (Kenobi’s “Surrender”)

-human trafficking (Zygerria/Trandosha)

-tragic/life-changing loss of a loved one (Steela Gerrera/Onderon)

-working under incompetent/cruel officers (Umbara)

-fighting in harsh environments (Mon Cala)

-Cronyism (Cpt Tarkin)

-Corruption (Cpt Argyus)

-being disavowed by the organization you gave your life to (Ahsoka’s trial)

-attempted assasination of enemy head of state (Obi-Wan undercover)

-Defecting (Lux Bonteri)

-High stakes rescue raid (The Citadel)

-Harebrained strategies working (Anakin)

-Civil unrest and domestic terrorism (Death Watch)

-High risk heliborne insertion (Geonosis)

-Human shields (Ryloth)

-Massive casualties (Storm over Ryloth)

-Biological Weapons (Blue Shadow Virus)

-attack on enemy superweapon (Malevolence)

The Clone Wars wasn’t a kid’s show. It was a deep look into how war affects all beings involved in conflict, the soldiers, civilians and politicians whose fates intertwine. I’m beyond thrilled that they’re giving us more of it.

-attempted assasination of enemy head of state (Obi-Wan undercover)

-Defecting (Lux Bonteri)

-High stakes rescue raid (The Citadel)

-Harebrained strategies working (Anakin)

-Civil unrest and domestic terrorism (Death Watch)

-High risk heliborne insertion (Geonosis)

-Human shields (Ryloth)

-Massive casualties (Storm over Ryloth)

-Biological Weapons (Blue Shadow Virus)

-attack on enemy superweapon (Malevolence)

The Clone Wars wasn’t a kid’s show. It was a deep look into how war affects all beings involved in conflict, the soldiers, civilians and politicians whose fates intertwine. I’m beyond thrilled that they’re giving us more of it.

title: Doggy See Doggy Do
description:
by youfluttermywings

Kylo’s terribly late for work, his dog Chewie is bleeding out from his leg and his regular vet is all booked out. The only vet who can fit him in is a forty minutes drive away…

Forget about the vet nurses, where did they hire these VETS?
A stunning brunette with a sharp face and gorgeous hazel eyes filled his vision. “Hello, I’m Dr Rey Smith. You can call me Rey. I’ll be your veterinarian today and look after Chewie.”
Kylo stood up from his seat and accepted the hand she offered. He towered over her, she was what five foot five, six maybe? Perfect cuddle size. Her hands were so smooth, and warm, he almost didn’t want to let go.

“Rrrrrruff!” Chewie’s loud bark startled them both. Kylo glared at his dog. Thanks Chewie for ruining the moment.

summary: For @michaelathewordsmith...based on several Taylor Swift songs listed in the tags. Enjoy! again, i cut down the amount bc of...
caption:
For @michaelathewordsmith…based on several Taylor Swift songs listed in the tags. Enjoy! again, i cut down the amount bc of how many songs

X marks the spot, where we fell apart (getaway car)

You felt numb. Everything that had happened in the last few days confused you. And it also hurt you.

Your boyfriend, Ben, disappeared. He took some fallen Jedi with him, sparing no one else…but his uncle.

Everything was different. He hadn’t told you about his plan to leave. He had never mentioned being discontent. Anytime he was with you, you thought the two of you were happy. 

And then…And then he was gone. And you abandoned.

I made up on my mind, I’m better off bein’ alone (kofh)

You chuckled while walking with Armitage. You had no idea why everyone else thought he was uptight. For you, he was the only one who was able to get you to forget the past. 

It had been a few years since it had happened, but Armitage was a blessing. He seemed to be desperate to make you happy.

“So, Y/N,” he started, clearing his throat.
“Yes?”
“I was wondering, hoping really, if you, if we could enjoy a dinner together, if you, if you wanted?”
You grinned at the man. “I would love that.”

Hold on to the memories, they will hold on to you (new years day)

“Ben?” you whispered, a lump caught in your throat.

The turned Jedi raised his masked gaze to you. Beneath the armor, he gasped and his body wanted to run to you. Except he couldn’t.

Hux had just stated that his fiancé was bringing him some papers. He had no idea that would be you. It was a good thing Hux already knew everything, though he kept quiet.

You were sure he was growing angry. That much you remembered about him. Of course, you weren’t about to let that bring you down. You love Armitage. Ben left…and seemed to be gone forever.

You strutted toward your fiancé, beaming at him. Turning, you reset your gaze to one of professionalism.

“I apologize for the lack of using a title. It won’t happen again Commander Ren.”
He grit his teeth. “As expected,” he forced himself to say.
“I…Congratulations on the engagement.”
You nodded briefly. “The compliment is appreciated.” Turning to Hux you said, “I’ll be returning to your office with some more things for you to sign.”

He smiled before nodding. Just like that, you had left the room. Ben had no idea what he was feeling. Maybe his father wasn’t the only attachment pulling him from his training.

Bridges burn, I never learn, at least I did one thing right
I did one thing right (ciwyw)

Armitage stood his ground against his superior.

“I understand how she feels about you,” he continued, “Because of that, I believe we should at least try and get along.”
“I have no reason to.”
Hux rolled his eyes. “Please, even with your mask I can tell you still love her.”

Ren remained silent.

“I’m just trying to do what’s best for her. Right now, she knows what that is, and that’s keeping it civil between the two of us.”

Ren grit his teeth. You and Armitage may think there could be a shared peace by leaving things as is, but he believed differently. He was going to get you back one way or another.

Oh how wrong he was.

This is why we can’t have nice things, honey (tiwwchnt)

summary: JJ Abrams Shares First Episode IX Set Photo
title: JJ Abrams Shares First Episode IX Set Photo
body:
The first set photo from ‘Star Wars: Episode IX’ has been released to social media by JJ Abrams.  There isn’t much to see since the focus is on the camera itself and not the action in front of it.  Still, you can make out Finn (John Boyega) and Chewbacca (Joonas Suotamo) in what appears to be the cockpit of the Millennium Falcon, and a mystery guest in the pilot’s seat…could it be Rey?  Abrams made note of the missing presence of Carrie Fisher and thanked Rian Johnson and George Lucas for what has come before.  ‘Star Wars: Episode IX will hit theaters December 20th, 2019.

Bittersweet starting this next chapter without Carrie, but thanks to an extraordinary cast and crew, we are ready to go. Grateful for @rianjohnson and special thanks to George Lucas for creating this incredible world and beginning a story of which we are lucky to be a part. #IX pic.twitter.com/FOfnGwVut5

— JJ Abrams (@jjabrams)
August 1, 2018
